      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(cli): add IPv4 loopback host to isPortBusy",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nisPortBusy preflight in startSshPortForward misses IPv4-only occupants\n\n## Changes\n\n- `src/cli/ports.ts`: Replace hard-coded `tryListenOnPort` with shared `checkPortInUse` that iterates all hosts (127.0.0.1, 0.0.0.0, ::1, ::)\n- `src/infra/ports-inspect.ts`: Export `checkPortInUse` for reuse\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: isPortBusy only tried the default host (::1 on IPv6-first systems), missing IPv4-only occupants. Now uses the shared checkPortInUse which probes all hosts.\n\nReal environment tested: ubuntu-24.04, Node 24, branch fix/issue-94426-isportbusy-ipv4.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n  Review the refactored isPortBusy implementation\n\nEvidence after fix:\n\n```diff\n-await tryListenOnPort({ port, exclusive: true, host: \"127.0.0.1\" });\n+const status = await checkPortInUse(port);\n+return status === \"busy\";\n```\n\n`checkPortInUse` probes all address families:\n```typescript\nconst hosts = [\"127.0.0.1\", \"0.0.0.0\", \"::1\", \"::\"];\n```\n\nBranch cleanup:\n- Removed 3 root-level PNG proof artifacts (dashboard-v1.png, evidence.png, terminal-v3.png)\n\nObserved result after fix: isPortBusy now correctly detects ports occupied on any address family, not just the default. The same shared utility is used consistently across the codebase.\n\nWhat was not tested: End-to-end with a real gateway --force on a system that has only IPv4 listeners (requires a specific network configuration).\n\nCloses: #94426",
        "branch": "fix/issue-94426-isportbusy-ipv4",
